National Union of Teachers has called for a ‘positive portrayal of same sex relationships’ in lessons to be made ‘compulsory’ under the next government . 
  MPs had a duty to tackle ‘homophobia, biphobia and transphobia’ Critics accused the NUT of ‘thought control’ and said the proposals risked ‘oversexualising’ children . 
